text: This charming 1942 ranch home with a modified English garden wall bond brick pattern, was designed by Jake Knapp and built by JR Womack in the heart of the Willo Historic District and located on one of its most sought-after streets. One thing you won't find in a home like this is a gigantic garage/workshop. If you are a car hobbyist, this may be the best deal downtown! Move in ready or ready for your personal aesthetic touches, this classic Willo home offers beautiful curb appeal and a traditional landscape that offers mature shade trees that leads you to the original front door and mailbox. As you enter, you'll discover gorgeous polished, integrally colored concrete floors, great trim work and large spacious rooms that are rare within this neighborhood. All new paint and fresh new bathroom and shower are just some of the improvements. As you enter, you'll discover gorgeous polished, integrally colored concrete floors, great trim work and large spacious rooms that are rare within this neighborhood. A huge front living room offers a great family comfort and a view to the front lawn. Corner windows in both the kitchen and living room offer a detail not seen in homes of this era. The kitchen has craftsman style oak cabinets and been beautifully remodeled to offer stone counters, excellent storage and direct access to the backyard. Windows have been replaced with dual pane insulated glass and home has been upgraded with newer gas fired furnaces and a gas fired tankless water heater. Charming historic details like the original milk bottle box by the back door where the homeowner could specify their order for the milkman to deliver. The backyard offers a nice blend of lawn and pavement for access to a gigantic, oversized air-conditioned and plumbed garage which could easily be transformed for a future casita with its own kitchen, bathroom, laundry or the added bonus of a detached office/studio. Perfect for working from home or creative endeavors. This home is perfect for urban living! As one of the first historic districts, Willo is only a breath away from the light rail, incredible dining, culture and all the amenities downtown Phoenix has to offer. It's not just a home but a piece of history ready to be cherished by its new owners. Embrace the blend of historical charm and modern convenience in this truly gorgeous landmark home. This lovely property is one not to miss. (Original 1942 blueprints of the home and detached conditioned space are available with the sale).

Discover an incredible opportunity to own a home in the highly desirable WILLO HISTORIC DISTRIC. This charming 3 bedroom, 1-bathroom property is being sold ''as is'' and is perfect for Buyers looking to add their own style and updates. There is a 2 car garage which could easily be converted to a guest quarters. Large kitchen and sperate laundry room with great storage. New bathroom sink just recently installed. Property is a C-O zone. Primarily office-type uses, such as: Professional offices (real estate, insurance, law, accounting, etc. Located right off Central Ave., you'll enjoy the unbeatable proximity to the light rail, restaurants, coffee shops and the vibrant arts districts

This rare offering features a 3-bedroom, 2-bath main home plus a fully detached 1-bedroom, 1-bath casita with kitchenette, private entrance, and its own A/C, all set within the coveted Willo Historic District. The main residence showcases original hardwood floors, a spacious living room with custom built-ins and a wood-burning fireplace, and abundant natural light through large windows, several upgraded to dual-pane. A formal dining room anchors the layout, while the galley kitchen includes granite countertops and ample cabinetry. Two bedrooms and a full bath are located upstairs, with a third bedroom and second full bath on the main level, offering flexibility for guests or multi-use living. Outdoors, the property feels like a private retreat with mature landscaping, a sparkling pool, and a relaxing hot tub. A paved patio is ideal for outdoor dining, all within a fully fenced yard with no alley access. The detached casita adds exceptional versatility for guests, extended family, or rental potential, while a one-car carport and extended driveway provide convenient off-street parking. A timeless Willo bungalow that blends historic charm, flexible living spaces, and resort-style amenities in one of Phoenix's most desirable neighborhoods.

WELCOME TO WILLO! This beloved family home is available for the first time in 53 years. Perfectly located on the iconic Palm Lane, this home offers beautiful curb appeal within this amazing neighborhood. Inside you will find a very spacious floor plan with large rooms and beautiful original details. This home also offers OWNED SOLAR and an extremely rare 3 CAR GARAGE. Cherished for so many years by the same family, this home is ready to be re-imaged and enjoyed for years to come. Home to be sold AS-IS making this the perfect opportunity to move in now and improve the home overtime to make it your dream home! Walking distance to all your Midtown favorites. Welcome Home!

Welcome to this beautifully maintained, adobe brick construction, Monterey Revival-style home located in the one and only Willo Historic District! This timeless home blends classic architectural details with thoughtful updates, offering warmth, vintage character, and inviting spaces throughout. From the moment you arrive, you're welcomed by curb appeal that includes lush water-wise yard landscaping and a charming front porch. Step inside to discover a spacious main living room featuring vaulted ceilings, Saltillo tile flooring, a gas fireplace, and expansive windows that fill the room with natural light. A graceful arched entry leads into the dining room, with a generous space for a large table-ideal for entertaining. The kitchen exudes vintage charm with checkerboard tile flooring, great condition, and a stylish tile backsplash. Beyond the kitchen, a laundry/pantry room offers ample storage potential. The 1,579 sq ft main home features two large storage closets, a beautifully preserved bathroom with original vintage tile, and two spacious bedroomseach with large closets and bright windows. Throughout the home, you'll find authentic historic details that have been thoughtfully maintained, including the original milk delivery door complete with a 'menu', indoor mail slot, and a built-in ironing niche that has been converted for spices. A bonus room with its own closet provides versatility and additional storageperfect for a home workspace, studio, or guest retreat. Enjoy seamless indoor-outdoor living with French doors leading to both the covered front porch and the spacious covered back patio and yard, ideal for relaxing or hosting gatherings. The property also includes a 634 sq ft detached guest house featuring one bedroom and one bathroom, with a private side entranceperfect for visiting guests, extended family, or potential income opportunity. This is home also benefits from the historic tax break as it is a contributing property. Close to the best that Downtown Phoenix has to offer, the airport, and freeways, this beautiful home truly checks all the boxes!

This 1926 Craftsman Bungalow offers the perfect blend of character and comfort, nestled in the coveted Roosevelt Historic District. Original wood floors, crown molding, and a welcoming front porch showcase the home's vintage charm, while thoughtful updates- like a tastefully remodeled kitchen and modern systems-make daily living easy. The layout features 3 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, a generous bonus room, and a 200 sq ft basement- plus a detached garage for added storage or creative space. The backyard is built for Arizona living, featuring a generous grassy lawn and a sparkling heated saltwater pool. All within walking distance to local dining, the arts scene, and your favorite downtown spots!

This stunning 1927 Tudor Revival nestled in the Willo Historic District exudes a perfect blend of charm and elegance, with a French-inspired flair and has been featured in Phoenix Home and Garden and the AZ Republic. The home's curb appeal is captivating, featuring a steep-pitched gable roof, an arched entry adorned with stone quoins and porte-cochre. Landscape artist Benjy Levinson designed the lush landscaping along with the quaint front patio and custom iron gates designed to echo the 1920s, which further enhance the property's charm. Known as the P.W. Womack house, named after its original owner, a prominent builder in town who also worked on projects like the Paradise Valley Country Club, this property boasts tall, coved ceilings and gorgeous original hardwood floors throughout. The beautiful living and dining rooms were refurbished by designer Christopher K. Coffin. The centerpiece of the formal living room with its soaring ceilings is the fireplace that has an original tile border and flanked by windows that flood the space with natural light. The dining room features a silver-leafed ceiling and navy walls, complemented by French doors that lead to a charming side patio. The sunny kitchen is a sweet space with gorgeous black-and-white striped wood floors, a brick-exposed wall, a vintage O'Keefe Merritt gas stove, and a charming breakfast nook. The separate family room offers a cozy retreat with a gas fireplace and seamlessly connects to an outdoor patio. The primary suite with views of the backyard and downtown high-rises beyond, provides a peaceful retreat with a serene cream-white color palette, including a claw-foot soaking tub in the bathroom. A rare feature in historic homes is the large, walk-in closet (designed by California Closets). The front guest bedroom overlooks the front yard, while the third bedroom is currently set up as an office. The charming guest bathroom features a cast iron tub enclosed in an original arched spaced. There is a separate large laundry room, with an inside storage room beyond. The home is powered by two separate AC/heating units. In the backyard, Levinson's design includes a fountain in the center, connected by formal walkways, a popular feature in French landscapes. The backyard also includes a built-in gas grill and covered dining/entertaining space. The inviting brick side patio, adorned with potted plants and a gas fireplace, is the perfect spot for coffee or happy hour. The convenient location makes it within walking distance to all the offerings of Midtown - great restaurants, museums, and light rail (Heard Museum) stop. With safety in mind, this home is not connected to a back alleyway. This lovely property is not one to miss. BRAND NEW roof and all new exterior paint!

HUGE PRICE DROP!! A rare opportunity in the heart of the Willo Historic District- Priced below market value, no HOA, can be a private casita, single story, large lot, and fully remodeled!! - This once-in-a-lifetime opportunity offers the perfect balance of historic charm and modern sophistication in one of Phoenix's most desirable neighborhoods. An inviting open-concept layout adorned with durable luxury vinyl flooring, white shaker cabinetry, and quartz countertops, creating a timeless yet contemporary feel. Every inch has been thoughtfully updated, offering style, comfort, and effortless living. complete with ample parking, a rarity in Willo. With a move-in ready presentation and a casita ideal for guests or income potential, this home stands apart as a true gem!! Dont let this slip aw

Roosevelt Historic - 1922 Neoclassical Revival on a quiet, palm-tree-lined street, designed&built by F.N. Holmquist-Phoenix's first civil engineer. This restored historic gem showcases preserved original details including wood floors, sash windows, doors, hardware, and fireplaces. Thoughtful updates featuring authentic reproduction kitchen and primary bath cabinetry, tankless water heater, updated electrical, copper plumbing, roof, 5 custom built doors from Iron Doors of Arizona and more. The spacious primary wing offers a custom tiled walk-in shower, dual sinks, and walk-in closet. Bedroom/bathroom w/ separate entrance downstairs. Outside entertain and enjoy with a Built in BBQ & Sparkling polished pebble tech pool w/ additional pop-ups, a large Baja step, AquaLink automation(see more) 3 water features, surrounded surrounded by Chicago brick. Bose outdoor speakers. Garage has upstairs loft,1/2 bath, workshop w/ large fans, traditional custom windows recessed speakers. & extra storage areas. Large custom rolling gate with 2 additional parking spots, Bose outdoor speakers. Commercial grade Titan alarm system with upstairs digital control panel, security cameras with a 360 view of outside. Walk or bike to dining, nightlife, and galleries in the Roosevelt Historic District. Qualifies for historic property tax deductions

WELCOME TO WILLO! This modernized 1950's ranch offers one of the best locations in Willo across from Walton Park. Beautiful landscaping and a large front courtyard welcome you upon arrival and invite your to enjoy this incredible neighborhood. As you enter the home, you'll discover fantastic upgrades have been done throughout to maximize this amazing home with so many designer details. Great floor plan with wonderful primary suite and a large living and dining room offers multiple doors and massive windows to enjoy the backyard. A huge covered patio offers an amazing outdoor kitchen, multiple seating areas and overlooks a beautiful fire pit patio with water features that make this backyard feel like a resort. Walking distance to all your Midtown favorites - Welcome Home!

Welcome To WILLO! Amazing location within walking distance to everything in Midtown! Enjoy skyline views from your front door within a neighborhood that feels like a small town in the city! This Red Brick Beauty offers great curb appeal with fantastic landscaping and so much charm! Inside you will find that Historic details have been preserved throughout with appropriate enhancements & beautiful designer upgrades. Original hardwood floors, classic archways, and a large red brick fireplace give it the WILLO charm you've been looking for! The kitchen offers granite counters, stainless steel appliances and designer details. Fantastic floor plan inside and outside offers great outdoor living with wonderful patio spaces and a full two car garage.

A truly exceptional home in the coveted Willo Historic District, this fully reimagined Mid-Century home blends timeless architecture with a complete modern transformation. Originally built in 1955, the home has undergone an extensive renovation, including raised 9 ft ceilings, opened walls, all-new electrical and plumbing, redesigned ductwork, and luxury upgrades throughout-creating a fresh, light-filled living experience rarely found in historic neighborhoods. Step inside to a beautifully executed open floor plan where the living, dining, kitchen, and family room flow seamlessly together. Designer Porcelanosa tile imported from Spain, architectural LED lighting, new dual-pane sliders, and custom finishes elevate every space. The chef's kitchen shines with Cafe appliances,... ...custom cabinetry, quartz countertops, Italian hand-blown lighting, and thoughtfully reconfigured electrical for modern living. Both bathrooms were fully rebuilt with high-end fixtures, custom vanities, luxury tile, upgraded glass, and spa-inspired details, including a Kohler steam shower in the primary suite. All bedrooms offer direct access to the outdoors, enhancing the home's serene indoor/outdoor connection. The backyard is a true private retreat, lush, quiet, and tailored for relaxation or entertaining. Enjoy a sparkling pool, built-in BBQ, custom planters, shaded patio spaces, and total privacy rarely found in the city. A drive-through garage plus a detached bonus room provides flexible space for a home office, art studio, gym, or creative workspace. Located on one of Willo's most desirable streets, this home places you steps from the Arts District, top restaurants, museums, and local coffee shops. A perfect blend of historic charm, modern luxury, and unbeatable walkability, this one-of-a-kind property is ready to welcome you home.

Welcome to 38 W Vernon...a stunning 3,100 sq ft residence in the heart of Phoenix's highly coveted Willo Historic District. This 3 bed + den, 3 bath home perfectly blends architectural integrity with modern updates. Original hardwood floors, arched doorways, and vintage fireplace details preserve the home's rich character, while a designer kitchen, smooth-textured walls, and a custom-built bar elevate everyday living. Upstairs, a color-drenched den/library offers the ideal creative retreat. Outside, enjoy a lush private backyard with a rare pool, mature landscaping, and space to entertain or unwind. All this just minutes from Roosevelt Row, Midtown dining, and Encanto Park. Willo homes with this combination of size, condition, and amenities rarely come to market..this one is truly special

Tudor Revival in the Heart of Historic Charm! Step into a 1925 red brick Tudor Revival like no other-reimagined for modern living with integrity, soul, and timeless style. Nestled in one of the most desirable historic neighborhoods, this one-of-a-kind home has undergone a thoughtful, year-long renovation, blending vintage character with today's comforts. Inside, you'll find oak hardwood floors, restored and glowing with warmth, paired with all-new plumbing, electrical, and sewer (plus updated systems) for true peace of mind. The fabulous kitchen and spa-worthy bathrooms shine with curated finishes and personality. Outdoors, enjoy a brand-new heated swimming pool, built-in grill, and lush, newly designed landscaping-an entertainer's dream. Need space for guests or creative projects? The spacious guest house is ready for anything...studio, office, or in-law suite. This home is full of charm, soul, and style, perfect for someone seeking authenticity, artistry, and a touch of rebellion from the ordinary. It's not just a home. it's a lifestyle. Welcome to something truly special.

Welcome to ROOSEVELT Historic District! Rare chance to own a 100-year-old Craftsman on a coveted palm-lined street in the Roosevelt Historic District. Offering 1,921 sq. ft. of living space, this property includes a two-bedroom, two-bath main home, an ensuite guest casita with kitchenette, and a separate office/studio on a large 9,250 sq. ft. lot. Features include a pool, wraparound porch, gated driveway, original built-ins, updated lighting, renovated baths, new appliances, solar panels, and lush landscaping. Architectural plans for a 500 sq. ft. expansion are included, and they have been approved by the City of Phoenix and the Historic District! Enjoy walkable access to Roosevelt Row, Hance Park, dining, arts, and light rail, plus low historic taxes and a welcoming community.

A chance to own a timeless home in the heart of Willo. Thoughtfully remodeled, this home blends historic character with tasteful modern updates while maintaining its charm. The main house offers 3 bedrooms and 2 bathrooms (1275sq ft), featuring white oak hardwood floors, a beautiful wood-burning fireplace, and an expansive kitchen with all new appliances, quartzite counters, a hand painted tile backsplash, and new Pella doors and windows. The detached casita (324sq ft) includes a bedroom and full bath, making it ideal for guests, a home office or a private Airbnb. The large backyard is equally inviting with turf, mature trees, and plenty of space to entertain. This home is a perfect fit for someone who values the character of a historic property while enjoying the comfort of modern living

This Landmark Estate formally named the ''Harry J. Felch House'' is a rare example of Dutch Colonial architecture in Phoenix.It retains an unheard of number of meticulously maintained original features from the front door with sidelights entering the formal foyer with custom faux finished etched plaster and ''dutch windmill'' light pendant that continue as you find yourself transported to a bygone era of grace and beauty.The main house features 5 bedrooms, three baths, formal,dining and breakfast rooms,office original kitchen/butler's pantry, modern kitchen and basement.The newly renovated carriage house hosts a two car garage and full guest house.The exquisite grounds feature a large pool,extensive gardens, mature trees,outdoor fireplace,pergolas and outdoor kitchen.Truly, a must see home

* Exceptional Urban Living in this Mid-Town Luxury Condo ** Updated 3 Bedrm 2 bath 1716 sq ft split floor plan ** Highlights Incl: Gourmet Kitchen, Granite Counters, Updated Cabinets, Anderson doors/windows. Wood Tile flooring, Contemporary Fireplace & Custom Lighting ! Primary Bdrm has separate shower & tub, 2 closets & access to Balcony ! 3rd bedrm makes a perfect den office / Study ** Amenities include clubhouse, theater room, pool, spa, sauna, gas grills, fitness center, underground/gated parking ( 2 spaces) that Downtown / Midtown has to offer ! Perfect location w/ direct access to light rail stop to fabulous restaurants, events & the endlessly growing Downtown Phx living experience including the ever Popular ''Roosevelt Row ''

text: Discover timeless luxury reimagined at The Bower Willo, a beautifully crafted two-story residence nestled in the vibrant heart of Midtown Phoenix. Blending classic architectural character with thoughtful modern comforts, this newly built home offers 1,901 sq. ft. of inspired living where warmth, craftsmanship, and community meet. Step inside to sunlit, open-concept spaces that invite connection and ease. The gourmet kitchen, designed for both everyday living and special gatherings, features quartz countertops, designer soft-close cabinetry, a full-height backsplash, and a professional Sub Zero/Wolf appliance suite. Gather in the flexible loft ideal for work or relaxation, or enjoy seamless indoor-outdoor flow to a charming private yard, perfect for alfresco dining under the Arizona sky. Every detail, from the Ring smart lock to custom laundry cabinetry, reflects thoughtful design and refined function. Refresh in exquisitely appointed baths with quartz dual vanities, frameless glass showers, and matte black Moen fixtures. Each space offers a serene, restorative ambiance that defines elevated everyday living. Throughout the home, warm luxury vinyl plank flooring, artisan finishes, and rounded Santa Fe details balance sophistication with comfort. Energy-efficient features such as a tankless water heater, Low-E dual-pane windows, and a pre-wired EV charger support an eco-conscious lifestyle. Set within a gated enclave inspired by the legacy charm of Phoenix's historic districts, The Bower Willo offers shared outdoor spaces, an outdoor kitchen, and lush landscaping, all within moments of Encanto Park, downtown dining, and cultural landmarks. Built by a master builder with over 55 years of award-winning expertise, this residence celebrates artistry, quality, and the enduring beauty of home. Experience the perfect blend of heritage charm and modern ease at The Bower Willo, where every detail feels personal, warm, and wonderfully crafted.

Step into a home that has been cherished by the same owner since the day it was built. Nestled in the heart of the Willo Historic District, this classic brick residence captures the warmth and character that make the neighborhood so loved. Inside, original details reflect a bygone era, while the inviting living spaces feel both comfortable and familiar. Two bedrooms and one bath provide a cozy retreat, and the generous backyard invites quiet mornings with coffee or lively evenings with friends. The solid brick exterior, mature landscaping, and timeless curb appeal make this a rare find. From here, tree-lined streets lead you to local cafes, boutique shops, and the vibrant energy of downtown Phoenix, all just moments away.

Stunning views in this 6th floor condo overlooking the pool below. Roosevelt historic district is one of the hottest neighborhoods in central Phoenix. The open floor plan is ''Loft style'' with no walls separating the living area from the bedroom. IT IS NOT A STUDIO. Travertine floors thru-out, full travertine shower, upgraded bath fixtures, granite counters and European style cabinets. Two-tone paint, upgraded light fixtures and all LED lighting TV swivels to bedroom Truly a turn-key residence for full time or ''lock-n-leave''.Watch the planes go to and from Sky Harbor and listen to the church bells on Sunday morning from your balcony. No other mid-century hi-rise like this in downtown. Furniture avail at no additional cost. Includes 1 covered parking space. Value priced for quick sale.

Penthouse Dreams in the Roosevelt Arts District. A rare opportunity to own one of a few true penthouses in Metro Phoenix. Set along the grass-and-tree-lined streets of the historic Roosevelt District, where mid-century style meets dramatic skyline and mountain views, this two-bedroom, two-bath penthouse spills out onto one of the largest penthouse balconies in the US. The balcony wraps around 2 sides of the building with unobstructed 270-degree views of the Phoenix skyline and mountain ranges that stretch more than fifty miles. Mornings feel cinematic, nights glow electric, and every sunset hits like a live art installation. Inside, floor-to-ceiling windows flood the home with natural light, blurring the line between indoors and out. The open layout flows easily from kitchen to living to balcony. It's a low-key trophy property, modern with soul. For the collector at heart, the seller who has called this building home since 1991 is offering something even rarer: the adjacent penthouse is also available, allowing both units to be combined into an expansive 2,704-square-foot dream home in the sky. Select artwork by Red-Chip artist Bill Dambrova is available for purchase, transforming this space into a living gallery. HOA fees include electricity, water, gas, sewer, trash, parking, hazard insurance and CAM. The building offers secure access, a pool area, and fitness center, steps from the vibrant Roosevelt Arts District, brimming with culture, dining, and nightlife. With a Walk Score of 92 and Bike Score of 87, this location defines convenience and connection. This isn't just a home, it's a flex, a statement, and a front-row seat to the city's evolution. Own the view. Own the vibe. Own the moment. Let your next chapter begin

Welcome to this stylish 1-bedroom, 1-bathroom condo located in the highly sought-after Roosevelt Row Historic District in Downtown Phoenix. With sleek polished concrete floors, exposed air vents, and a clean urban-chic aesthetic, this home perfectly blends industrial character with modern comfort. Updated kitchen and bathroom feature contemporary finishes, while the open layout offers versatile living space filled with natural light. Enjoy the vibrant lifestyle of downtown-just steps from trendy restaurants, bars, coffee shops, and art galleries. Take a refreshing dip in the sparkling community pool on hot summer days. This is the perfect place for those who love modern style and city living.

Stunning completely remodeled Midtown luxury condo at the desirable Tapestry on Central. Well maintained 2 bedroom and 1.75 bath with modern upgrades. Two side-by-side parking spaces in gated underground garage. Spacious kitchen with plenty of cabinet storage, new countertops, stainless steel appliances and pantry. New LVP floors and tile throughout (no carpet). Large laundry room off kitchen with full side-by-side washer/dryer and room for storage. Relaxing bright open living room to enjoy with family and friends. Covered balcony with courtyard views. Easy to enjoy amenities such as pool, spa, sauna, fitness center and club house. Great location! Near light rail station. Walking distance to restaurants, museums and other entertainment.This is a must see!
